The All Progressive Congress (APC) Governors’ Forum has rated Kano State Governor, Dr Abdullahi Umar Ganduje as the best in initiating and executing developmental projects. Addressing a press conference yesterday, the Chief Press Secretary to the governor, Abba Anwar said the governor has topped the list of the forum’s performance assessment for three consecutive months of September, October and November. Anwar said a letter dated October 7, 2019 and signed by the Director General of the Forum, Salihu Mohammed Lukman, indicated that there was an all-round increase in the pattern of initiatives introduced by the APC-led states with Kano recording the most initiatives for the Month (September) with eighteen (18) strides, spreading across empowerment, healthcare, education, security, transportation, welfare, power, agriculture, justice and sensitisation.” The letter revealed that, Yobe follows with 14 strides, Borno with 13, while Edo, Gombe, Kaduna, Lagos and Ogun states have 12 strides each. Furthermore, Ekiti State recorded 11 strides, Nasarawa 9, Katsina and Kebbi states 7 each, Kwara and Osun 6 each and Niger state follows with 5 strides respectively, Ondo has 4 strides, while Kogi and Plateau states have 3 strides each. He said some of the indices given for Kano’s emergence across the mentioned developmental areas are that the state trains 60 youths on maintenance of high duty and articulated vehicles, and distributed 8 million mosquito nets, coupled with the governor’s unrelenting commitment in universal health coverage, among others.  APC governors rate Ganduje best governor in developmental projects APC governors forum rates Ganduje best performing governor JUST IN: Ganduje gets 'Best Governor’ award